This paper deals with the topic of providing explanations for robotic actions, which falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the social science aspect of generating effective explanations, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The methods presented for generating contrastive explanations involve machine learning techniques, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and possibly also under social and information networks (cs.SI).
